race.comment: Tough race. INVINCIBLE AMOUR (4) was a smart winner on debut at Yarra Valley over 1009m, showing good speed and coming clear to score by 1.3 lengths. Didn't beat much and this is obviously deeper but it's certainly winnable and she can measure up. SPIRAL DREAM (14) resumes. She won on debut at Moe leading throughout, sent straight for a spell. She draws the pole and with natural improvement can win again. LLOYD'S CROWN (2) only had one run last time in and struggled in a stronger race at Sandown Hillside. He doesn't win out of turn but his best form reads well. PER IVY (5) is racing consistently and was close up at Cranbourne last time out without much luck which reads well.
